Avoid calling `setState` from inside a loop as each call to `setState` will result in a render. 

Instead assemble the `imageChosen` array first, and then pass it to `setState`. Also since you&#39;re not modifying the files array you should just be able to pass it directly to `setState` without looping through it.

Also keep in mind [state updates may be asynchronous](https://reactjs.org/docs/state-and-lifecycle.html#state-updates-may-be-asynchronous)

